<HL>
   Uniroyal Says U.S. Backs
   Acquisition by Michelin
</HL>
<DATE>
04/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   F.MIC
</CO>
<IN>
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<GV>
JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)
</GV>
<LP>
   AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- The federal government has decided to
allow Michelin Group to proceed with its planned $1.5 billion
acquisition of Uniroyal Goodrich Tire Co., according to
Uniroyal.
   The tire maker said it was informed of the decision by the
Justice Department's antitrust division.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Michelin, based in France, last September said it would
pay $690 million in cash and assume $810 million in debt to
acquire Uniroyal Goodrich, creating the world's largest tire
maker.
</TEXT>
